    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A sports drink recipe calls for <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="4281">\(\frac{5}{3}\)</span> tablespoons of powdered drink mix for every 12 ounces of water. How many batches can you make with 5 tablespoons of drink mix and 36 ounces of water? Explain your reasoning.<presentation-tag data-tag-title="2 INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/5.tag"></presentation-tag></p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>3 batches. Each batch has <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="4281">\(\frac{5}{3}\)</span> tablespoons of drink mix, so 3 batches will have 5 tablespoons of drink mix, since <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45254">\(3 \boldcdot \frac{5}{3} = 5\)</span>. Similarly, we can make 3 batches with 36 ounces of water, since <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="41082">\(3 \boldcdot 12 = 36\)</span>.</p>
</div>
